MATATIELE police arrested two suspects aged 26 and 36 after they were found in possession of two bags of dagga on Tuesday. They were arrested in Station Road in Matatiele at 3pm. SAPS spokesperson Captain Raphael Motloung said both have been charged with dealing in dagga. They appeared in court yesterday (Thursday) and at the time of going to press the case had not been concluded. Matatiele Station Commander Maphelo Ngame thanked police for working hard to arrest the suspects. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.